th, and other policy areas, this book develops a conceptual framework for analyzing these issues. It explores the tradeoffs in measuring performance, the methods of communicating results effectively to mass and elite audiences, and the ways in which organizations respond to the data gathered.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aOrganizational effectivenessxEvaluation. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh1 aWeimer, David L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674272989zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674272989423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674272989/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK